anonymous 2 weeks ago

do you have any tips for keeping fics cohesive? ive been writing for about 2 years but i still struggle with writing longer fics because i tend to forget details/not plan ahead (tbh i dont even know how to do that) and it makes writing so much harder

I can only speak to my experience, because I’m not entirely sure what kind of writer you are so I won't be able to cater to that specifically, sorry. And also please take all of this with a grain of salt, I’m no professional, just someone who writes as a hobby.

I am not a planner. This might be appalling to some people, but I did not plan a single thing about my most recent soulmates yunki fic despite the fact that it's 75k. I tend to write scenes as they come to me, whenever they come to me. I also write out of order. Obviously as the fic progresses, the puzzle pieces start falling together and I can see more of the entire picture: where I want the story to go, how I want it to conclude, etc.

For me, writing usually starts with a general idea/conflict or a scene that's stuck in my head. I don't know if you've read any of my fics or which ones you've read, so I'll try to be specific when I use examples. Take my a/b/o yunki fic for instance, that fic was born because I wanted to explore the conflict between the familial view of yunki versus a romantic view, and what would happen if Jake felt that familial to romantic shift internally and was struggling with it.

Now to keep a fic cohesive despite not planning ahead, I focus on the idea that came into mind, and try to visualize the full character/conflict arc I want them to experience. In the a/b/o yunki fic, that was, to put it simply, Jake going from feeling guilty and shameful, to coming to terms with and accepting his romantic feelings for Riki. Therefore, every scene I wrote fell somewhere along that arc, and was focused on propelling that development forward. That way, while I might not have had the scenes preplanned, I only wrote scenes that fit the arc I was trying to tell. This is also the case even for some of my pwp works, like my heeyunki one, where yes it was mostly sex, but I still had some sort of before and after in mind for heeyunki's relationship that I shaped the story around.

For the little details, for things I might want to call back to in a later scene to tie things together, I will note (mentally but also sometimes in the doc itself) what symbols, dialogue, actions, etc. Feel meaningful so that I can refer to them later. Additionally, if there's a plot point or character arc you want to make sure you give closure to, highlight it, note it down, do something to remind yourself of it while you're writing. Because I don't plan ahead, making sure I’m cognizant of plot points and character development as I write is important. I’m constantly taking into account where the character/plot currently is, and where I want it to go, and then each scene I write is me bridging that gap.

Honestly that last part is basically my writing logic. "Here is where the story is right now, there is where I think it should go, what do I have to write to get there?" Also because I write out of order, many times I have to write backwards: "Here is where the story is right now, this is where it was, what needs to have happened to have gotten here?" There are of course many times where I have no idea where the story is going or where it came from, I just have a scene. Those times, I just take one step forward. "This is where the conflict/character is right now, where can it go from here?" And then I have to sit and brainstorm what sort of development I want. Sometimes I can only think of one way forward, but other times I find multiple and then I have to choose which one is the most compelling and that I can see some sort of light at the end of the tunnel with.

Moral of the story: The way I keep fics cohesive is by focusing on the central theme/idea/conflict/character arc that I want this fic to show the before and after of. It doesn't need to be a drastic before and after, but I specifically write to move that arc forward. If I never lose sight of the arc of the story, which I guess is kind of the "moral" or "point" of the story, then I find that my fics tend develop cohesively without my needing to pay extra attention to cohesiveness.

what are your thoughts/analyses/observations on the 02z dynamic (in an rps way)? i always find them so interesting because they all treat each other slightly differently underneath the general chaos

love this question. i have a previous post with some thoughts on them [here, it's the first screenshot] but let me expand on it.

general chaos is very true, 02z are the most chaotic trio out of enha and it fills me with joy. non-rps for a second, but their friendship and bond is one of my favorite things about enha and that sports day en-o'clock where they were on the same team is so fucking funny. 02z moments are seriously the funniest.

back to rps. okay so i think i'll just tackle this by duo and then all three of them together?

first up, jayke. jayke are definitely the bickerers out of the three but that's because jake refuses to relent or pick his battles. like sunghoon is good at relenting to others and deciding what hill he wants to die on (very few, actually, he's quite agreeable and will just give in or give up eventually), but jake is very much ready to fight every time jay looks his way. it's usually jay who will give in despite how stubborn he can be, but it's quite cute of him. i think they like the push and pull, look forward to it even, though usually jay looks exasperated by the end (my poor, overworked husband vs spoiled wife jayke agenda, i'm sorry i'll stop).

one of my favorite things is how shy jake gets the moment jay is nice or sweet or gentle with him (or if jay looks him in the eye/gets close to him, he's so shy about eye contact it's crazy). like he fully malfunctions and it's so funny, and then he just gets bristly to cover it up. i also love that jay has like no idea how to deal with jake sometimes, this dude who refuses to back down in needling him no matter how annoyed he gets and he's not even cute about it (like jungwon) and he refuses to let jay live. i think they annoy each other because they can't stand how attractive the other person is and how much they want them, so they just convert it into aggressive energy/bickering. they're the: i'm going to punch you in the mouth with my mouth, softly, because i love you. or however that phrase goes. that's jayke. they think they're arguing and then they get their hands on each other and huh, that's interesting, how did we end up in bed together again?

in contrast, jayhoon definitely also bicker but their arguments don't feel like. childish or petty the way jayke's do because jayke argue about everything and anything. but jayhoon are more like 'move your fucking elbow off the table, i don't have any space, omfg how many times do i have to tell you that?' and then the other person gets defensive, and then they're annoyed for like 2 minutes, and then it's wrapped up. but the arguments r like. legitimate. jayhoon have held a special place in my heart since jay said

'my one and only unit, sunghoon-ah. i'm not good with words, but i really like you'

i am a Sucker for that shit (see: sunjake, aka crownz, aka 'i've known sunoo longest'). also jay and sunghoon are quite tender with each other, i think on a more regular basis than jayke or even jakehoon, but they're just more lowkey about it and their bickering catches attention instead. that one clip of jayhoon where sunghoon is up on stage mcing and jay is smiling so fucking fondly at him? yeah, kill me now. also i really love how sunghoon has the time of his life teasing jay but is also very sensitive to his moods and will immediately start backing off the moment jay looks upset (unlike a certain someone cough jake cough). he's really attentive to jay, and their understanding of each other's personalities and tendencies melts my heart. idk u can just see how fond they are of each other in any enha content, it makes me want to scream into the void. they match each other's energy but somehow also contrast the other perfectly? black & white is really such an apt chemi name for them. doe 11/12/2024

mtl likely. who in enha do u think would find the idea of a situationship very attractive?

okay i'll do the ranking first then the justification:

most to least

  1. jake
  2. sunoo
  3. heeseung
  4. jungwon
  5. niki
  6. jay
  7. sunghoon

justification:

i went about ranking this from least to most likely actually, because i feel like i can more confidently pick out who is least interested in a situationship.

i think sunghoon tops that list because he seems like someone who dedicates themselves to someone or something fully and a situationship works against his interests. like if you're in a situationship with sunghoon, it's definitely a one-sided thing because he's gonna be fully invested in you and he's really just following your pace. like lock that man down, stop playing games.

jay is next because he's romantic and sensitive and kind, and i don't think the back-and-forth and if's and but's of a situationship mesh with his personality. he's just not like that, he cares too deeply. he's basically tied with sunghoon, i just put sunghoon lower because i think he's more intense and direct about his dedication/devotion, whereas jay is shyer and subtler about it. also he has his moments of pride, so he might pretend he's fine with a situationship.

niki is less overtly dedicated/devoted compared to jayhoon, but i do think he's more obsessive (positive) so i don't really see how a situationship works for him either. he knows what he wants. only reason he's higher than jayhoon, and more likely to be in a situationship, is cause i think he'd just find it fun to mess around with the other person a little. he's still young, he's still fucking around. but when he makes up his mind, there's no changing it.

jungwon is above niki, jay, sunghoon because i don't think he takes romance or sex as seriously but i also feel like he'd avoid a situationship on practicality alone. like he doesn't have time for this tbh. he has a group to worry about, he doesn't need their dynamics getting fucked up because a situationship ends wrong. also he might not take romance that seriously but he's still a bit possessive, so a situationship kind of just? doesn't make sense to him? like let's just agree you're mine and move on.

heeseung thinks he's fine, thinks it's all fun and games until he catches deep feelings. he's like i can keep emotion and sex separate, this gray area stuff isn't gonna get to me, and then it does. in theory he's down with situationships, in practice... not so much. poor guy.

sunoo just dgaf tbh. i feel like he's fine because he has a good handle on compartmentalizing, so a situationship is like eh, whatever to him. kind of interesting, kind of amusing, he's wondering when the other person is gonna crack. i think if he really felt something for the other person, he wouldn't allow himself to get trapped into a situationship. so if he is in this hazy, undefined, 'hey what are we?' stage, he's probably the one avoiding the 'let's put a label on this' conversation because he's not as invested as the other person. and honestly i support him.

okay first of all, i feel like jake also gets himself into situationships unknowingly because he's so free with his affection and attention but also at the same time quite guarded/emotionally unavailable. so you don't really know where you stand with him. but also i think he would find situationships like the perfect middle of i get all this affection and attention from you and i get to show it to you as well, but we don't need to be emotionally vulnerable with each other. i don't need to open myself up anymore than i want to. it's funny cause he generally is considered the most (or at least top 2 most) affectionate, friendly, kind, attentive member in enha by enha themselves, but he's also self-confessed to be guarded, so that dichotomy to me is interesting. i think that contradiction suits situationships the most, which is why he's at the top for me.
